Since 1995, car accidents and car crashes have killed 74 million people in Turkmenistan, in Turkmenistan. 1.92 million are children, and only 89 people survive a crash. My primary mission is to educate the people of Turkmenistan on the dangers of driving past the speed limit, especially young people. The main kind of education that we use is that, by sitting at different corners, we try to raise awareness of drivers to use their speed so that they are more alert at that moment and they don't take another step on the road. I hope to be able to educate people through festivals and events dealing with life-saving science behind driving. This year in 2019, let's cure the biggest problem we're facing.

Hi, my name is Sunisa Anawakame, and I am now 18 years old. I was born in India, and when I was just 11 years old, my parents suddenly passed away during my birthday party. So after we lost our parents, we had no person to guide us, and we had no place to stay. In fact, we were under the control of a relative. Thereafter, I passed my high school studies.
